UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='I did not hesitate to incinerate it to dust, and I now I regret doing so. But I was able to prove my unprovoked theory, that the corpse (and by extension the plague that saturates it) was indeed waiting for further commands. It\'s clear that those who die by this plague are only lying dormant in their graves, awaiting one skillful in necromancy to awaken them.$B$B In short, it is indisputable that the plague is magical in nature.' WHERE `word_id` = 126966; -- locales_page_text - text : entry=3440
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='Liferoot:$B$BThis may be gathered from the wilderness, or gained from the Withervine Beasts of Dustwallow Marsh. It\'s power will be necessary to draw the life essence of Cyclonian to this world.' WHERE `word_id` = 124982; -- locales_page_text - text : entry=856
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='Oct 18.$B$BI\'ve stumbled upon a key factor of this plague, one so cleverly hidden in its methodology that I\'ve come to two immutable conclusions: That its development was for the singular purpose of ending human life, and its inception was at the hands of an intelligent being. $BLong term affliction of the plague causes a certain reanimation of activity in the dead. This activity is very small at first, and I disregarded it as a minor side-effect. However, this energy remained persistent and unwavering. A thought struck me, one which was both surprising and strong: The corpse was waiting for something.' WHERE `word_id` = 126964; -- locales_page_text - text : entry=3438
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='The impure, rundown barbarians will be judged next; That\'s how it should be. Praise be the light! Please, Revered High General, tell our brothers and sisters about this miracle. May the light be with you forever, so that you may spread the good news to the end of the day! Respectfully, D. Adams "The Closing ..."' WHERE `word_id` = 269137; -- locales_page_text - text : entry=3112
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='To all able-bodied men and women:$B$BThe Scourge have returned and we must set aside our squabbles to face this threat. The Argent Dawn will turn away none who wish to take arms against the Scourge menace.$B$BThose who would defend our lands are mustering at Light\'s Hope Chapel in the Eastern Plaguelands. Together, we shall prevail.$B$BKeeper of the Rolls$BThe Argent Dawn' WHERE `word_id` = 125739; -- locales_page_text - text : entry=2872
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='Today the Syndicate holds little power in these lands, but they know the area well and have assembled sufficient manpower for the tasks ahead. With proper guiding I am confident that soon, the Syndicate will again rule Alterac.$B$BIn addition, we have urged the Syndicate to aim for the city of Stromgarde in the nearby Arathi Highlands. The city is a battlefield between our forces, ogres and the humans of Stromgarde, but we feel that with careful tactics we will own this once great city.' WHERE `word_id` = 124693; -- locales_page_text - text : entry=258

